A 37-year-old man was arrested when he was found with copper
cables weighing more than 1240 kilograms. He was arrested in an intelligence driven operation that was
conducted at Ogocini area near Matigulu Bridge in Nyoni by the Eshowe Crime
Intelligence Unit. A homestead which fitted the same description given to the
police officer, was identified and searched. According to the cops the suspect could not give
satisfactory explanation about the copper cables. He was then arrested and charged accordingly. The police say they believe that the suspect might be
involved in a number of copper cable thefts in the province. The arrested suspect will appear in the Nyoni Magistrateâ€™s
Court on Tuesday facing charges of possession of property suspected to be
stolen. The street value of the property is more than R64 000. 